  "text": "Intramyocellular lipid (IMCL) accumulation has been shown as a factor related to decreased insulin sensitivity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Obese insulin sensitive children and adolescents present lower levels of visceral fat and IMCL when compared with obese insulin resistant children [CITATION_3] . Furthermore, higher IMCL has been reported in obese children with IGT when compared with normal glucose tolerance (32), suggesting a pathogenetic role of IMCL in the development of insulin resistance and IGT.",
